<title>USA: MetaTools, Fractal merger completed.</title>
<headline>MetaTools, Fractal merger completed.</headline>
<dateline>CARPINTERIA, Calif. 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>MetaTools Inc and Fractal Design Corp said Thursday that shareholders of both companies approved their merger.</p>
<p>The approval made the merger complete, forming MetaCreations Corp.</p>
<p>Under the terms of the merger, Fractal shareholders received 0.749 MetaTools shares for each Fractal share held. The merger is being accounted for as a pooling of interests.</p>
<p>The combined company expects to incur a charge of about $9 million in the quarter ending June 30 to reflect costs relating to the transcation.</p>
<p>MetaCreations makes desktop visual computing software.</p>
